 The arrests were effected  by the Middelburg Stock Theft Unit, together with ACSU Security and famers, after information was received. During the operation, three cattle trucks, two loaded with cattle and one busy loading, were discovered in the Breyten area. Altogether 122 cattle were already loaded onto the trucks, while 57 cattle were ready to be loaded and more cattle were being chased into a kraal. Also read: Krugersdorp sakeman gearresteer vir veediefstal Brig. Leonard Hlathi, police spokesperson, said that a 32 year-old lawyer as well as another man was arrested on the scene. Several suspects ran away. Police also confiscated a Toyota Hilux bakkie and R95 000 cash on the scene. One of three trucks transporting the stolen cattle. Futher investigations resulted in the arrest of ten more suspects, whom police believe supplied the stolen cattle. Also read: Boere moedeloos gesteel Brig. Hlathi also said that two men and a woman, who looked after the cattle, were tied up and held up during the cattle theft. Ten other suspects were later taken into custody. The suspects will appear in court tomorrow and will face charges of stock theft and the possession of stolen property. Their names cannot be made public before their court appearance.     Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za 